headline: Stock Market Today: Nasdaq, S&P 500 Add Gains But Small Caps Lag; Fed Makes Expected Rate Cut (Live Coverage)
summary: The stock market closed mostly higher Thursday but trimmed some gains in afternoon trading after the Federal Reserve cut interest rates by a quarter point, as expected.  The Dow Jones Industrial Average ended flat.  The Fed did what everyone expected: It lowered the fed funds rate by 25 basis points to a range of 4.50% to 4.75%.

headline: AppLovin stock soaring over 40% on Q3 earnings, guidance
summary: Shares of AppLovin (APP) are flying higher on Thursday, shooting above 44% after topping third quarter earnings estimates and raising its fourth quarter guidance. Notably, the company saw its sales increase 39% year-over-year in the third quarter. Market Domination's Julie Hyman and Josh Lipton review the analyst commentary around the application software company's quarterly performance. headline: Applovin, Match Group, Adyen: 3 Stocks In Focus
summary: App publisher Applovin (APP) is seeing its stock skyrocket by nearly 50% after raising its fourth quarter guidance and seeing sales increase 39% annually in its third quarter. Match Group (MTCH) — whose brand portfolio of dating apps include Tinder, Hinge, and Match.com — shares slump after lowering its fourth quarter guidance, noting paying customers for app services fell 3% in its latest quarter. Online payment processor Adyen (ADYYF) reported slowing transaction volume growth while seeing sales grow 21% in its third quarter. To watch more expert insights and analysis on the latest market action, check out more Morning Brief here. This post was written by Luke Carberry Mogan.
